                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18160529-102-off539 t18160529-102-crimeloc542"></join>. On the evening of the day in the indictment, I was in my parlour behind my shop, and was alarmed by the sound of one of the tin stands (on which we generally place the hams) falling. I ran out, and the watchman had seized the prisoner with the ham before he had crossed the threshold.</p>
